found I could attain or improve. I am a Finance Major and, being that it is a financial company, I was interested in knowing what I could improve on. Unfortunately, they did not respond after I was sent notice of not being selected. It's not a big deal, BUT after a lengthy interview process, I hoped they could've at least provided some sort of feedback along with the decision.Interview Questions They asked basic questions over skill sets and level of expertise. They also asked questions like "what are three areas of your skill set that need improvement." I found their questions were formed to find out more of one's weak points rather than discussing strong attributes and skills. I   Answer Question GV Financial 2016-11-02 07:50 PDT See All 3 Interviews GV Financial Awards & Accolades+ Add Awards300 Top Registered Investment Advisers, Financial Times, 2014Top U.S. Registered Investment Advisors, Financial Advisor, 2014 2014300 Top Registered Investment Advisers, Financial Times, 2014Top U.S. Registered Investment Advisors, Financial Advisor, 2014America's Top Financial Advisors(CEO - David Geller), Barron's, 2014Top Financial Advisors(CEO - David Geller), Barron's, 2014Top 100 U.S. Registered Investment Advisors, WealthManagement.com, 2014 2013RIA Ranking, Financial Advisor, 2013 2012Top 1000 U.S. Financial Advisors(CEO David Geller), Barron's, 2012Top 25 Georgia Financial Advisors(CEO - David Geller), Barron's, 2012 2009Leadership Character Award(CEO - David Geller), Turknett Leadership Group, 2009See MoreSee LessWork at GV Financial? Share Your ExperiencesGV FinancialStarVery DissatisfiedStarDissatisfiedStarNeutral ("OK")StarSatisfiedStarVery Satisfied  Click to RateStart your review...orAdd a SalaryAdd BenefitsAdd an InterviewAdd a SalaryAdd BenefitsAdd an InterviewCloseOutline of two peoples' headsWork in HR or Marketing?Grow your employer brandGet a free employer accountCompanies to Explore Job Seekers Also ViewedMerialStarStarStarStarStar 107 ReviewsAir Product