										Born & Raised
										

Atlanta, Georgia

										Family
										

Marc is married to Bev Saltzman Lewyn, a former CNN researcher and co-author of "On the Run in Nazi Berlin." Marc and Bev live in Atlanta with their four amazing daughters.

										Favorite...
										

Marc has an odd fascination with baseball statistics and worked as a teenager for the Atlanta Braves as an usher and grounds crew, where he saw Hank Aaron’s 715th home run.  Marc also loves sailing – he almost won a major amateur sailing competition as a teenager, but alas, he learned a great life lesson instead, namely “It’s never over until it’s over.”

										Fun Fact
										

Marc occasionally coaches amateur wrestling and won a wrestling scholarship to the University of Virginia. While there, he also was the Editorial Page Editor of "The Cavalier Daily" and ended up working for a U.S. Senator from Florida. Marc is a recovering lawyer and a secret juggler.

										Favorite Quote	
										

										“If you have an important point to make, don't try to be subtle or clever. Use a pile driver. Hit the point once. Then come back and hit it again. Then hit it a third time – a tremendous whack.”  − Winston Churchill										



















