GV Financial Advisors – Introducing a New Era: Behavioral Wealth Management
June 14, 2017by AdvisoryHQ














GV Financial Advisors – Introducing a New Era: Behavioral Wealth Management





GV Financial Advisors Review (Overview)





GV Financial Advisors is an independent Registered Investment Advisor that was founded by David and Matthew Geller in 1991 as a result of the founders’ belief that conventional investment advisory firms largely ignore the human factor – how the brain and emotions affect client financial behavior and decision-making.


In 2005, GV Financial Advisors began developing the founding principles of Behavioral Wealth Management, a unique advisory model that incorporates wealth management, stress and decisions, life events expertise, and its “passion for the human factor,” which accounts for human emotions as part of the wealth management process.





Image source: GV Financial 


GV Financial Advisors is a strong believer in guiding clients on their journey to financial success through a unique perspective on how clients’ wealth can help them navigate critical life decisions – a perspective that goes far beyond the traditional “number crunching” that most other advisory firms subscribe to.


Since Behavioral Wealth Management extends far beyond your everyday traditional wealth management, GV Financial Advisors aims to create a completely different perspective for their clients.


They state, “We’re here to do more than simply help you build your wealth. Our deeper mission is to help you USE your wealth to create the life you desire.”


	 


A crucial element of the GV Financial Advisors’ philosophy is the belief that advisors should work closely with their clients to guide them through crucial, life-changing personal and professional decisions, which may be brought about as a result of life events that can have significant impacts on clients’ wealth, as well as their quality of life.





Image source: GV Financial


GV Financial Advisors is staffed by a team of loyal, long-standing employees that assure clients of continuity of service, with the average tenure of a GV employee (as of Feb. 2015) being nearly 10.5 years. GV Financial Advisors also has a unique team structure. With other financial advisors or wealth managers, a client is often assigned to only one advisor. At GV, you get a whole team. The firm’s entire culture is built around teams.












Accolades and Recognition


GV Financial Advisors has won numerous awards and accolades from its peers and industry watchers, including:



Being listed in REP's Top 100 U.S. Registered Investment Advisors in 2014 (advisory firms are ranked by total assets)


Listed for the fourth time among the top national registered investment advisors by Financial Advisor magazine


Named in the 2014 Financial Times’ "FT 300 Top Registered Investment Advisers" list


CEO David Geller’s recognition by Barron’s magazine as one of America's top financial advisors and among the top 30 in Georgia


…and many others!



Catering to high-net-worth individuals and privately-owned businesses and their families, a 2014 industry ranking placed GV Financial Advisors as the 98th largest independent registered investment advisor in the United States, with over $1.3 billion in assets under management as of January 30, 2015.






